microprocessor_definition.name: Screen Dial
microprocessor_definition.description: Displays a dial on a screen.

node.label: Input Number
node.description: The number to display.

object.script:
-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() inVal = input.getNumber(1) x = input.getNumber(2) y = input.getNumber(3) min = input.getNumber(4) max = input.getNumber(5) rad = input.getNumber(6) fac = factor() end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() cx = x cy = y + rad
screen.setColor(255, 255, 255) drawDialFace()
screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) angle = math.pi * (1 - fac) p0x = cx + math.cos(angle) * rad * 0.9 p0y = cy - math.sin(angle) * rad * 0.9 screen.drawLine(cx, cy, p0x, p0y)
screen.setColor(0, 100, 5) str = string.format("%.0f%%", fac * 100) strW = string.len(str) * 5 screen.drawText(x - math.floor(strW * 0.5) + 1, cy + 3, str)
--text Title screen.drawText(1,1,"Thrtle") end
function drawDialFace() screen.drawLine(x + rad, y + rad, x - rad, y + rad)
angle = 0 step = math.pi / 4
for i = 0, 3, 1 do p0x = cx + math.cos(angle) * rad p0y = cy - math.sin(angle) * rad p1x = cx + math.cos(angle + step) * rad p1y = cy - math.sin(angle + step) * rad
screen.drawLine(p0x, p0y, p1x, p1y) angle = angle + step end end
function factor() range = max - min
if range > 0 then return (inVal - min) / (max - min) else return 0 end end

bg = {r=5, g=5, b=5, t=150} --background color tx = {r=0, g=100, b=5, t=250}
function round(num, dec) local mult = 10^(dec or 0) return math.floor(num * mult + 0.5) / mult end
-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() SPD = round(input.getNumber(1)*1.94384449, 1) ALT = round(input.getNumber(2)) VET = round(input.getNumber(3)*3.2808399,1) BEA = round(((-input.getNumber(4)*360)+360)%360,2) LG = input.getBool(1) LL = input.getBool(2) AP = input.getBool(3) ALTH = input.getBool(4) SPEEDWARN = input.getBool(5) ALTWARN = input.getBool(6) XWARN = input.getBool(7) YWARN = input.getBool(8) AUTOTWARN = input.getBool(9) BATTWARN = input.getBool(10) FLASH = input.getBool(11) APWARN = input.getBool(12) AHWARN = input.getBool(13) end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight()
--Warning System if BATTWARN == true then BATTWARNstr = "!!LOW BATTERY!!" else BATTWARNstr = "" end if SPEEDWARN == true then SPEEDWARNstr = "!!LOW SPEED!!" else SPEEDWARNstr = "" end if SPEEDWARN == true then FLASHSPDstr = 155 else FLASHSPDstr = 1 end if BATTWARN == true then FLASHBATTstr = 155 else FLASHBATTstr = 1 end
--Start up Text if ALTWARN == true then ALTWARNstr = "--ENTER DESIRED ALTITUDE--" else ALTWARNstr = "" end if ALTWARN == false and XWARN == true and YWARN == true then XYWARNstr = "--ENTER DESIRED CO-ORDINATES--" else XYWARNstr = "" end if ALTWARN == false and XWARN == false and YWARN == false and APWARN == false then APWstr = "--ENGAGE AUTO PILOT--" else APWstr = "" end if ALTWARN == false and XWARN == false and YWARN == false and APWARN == true and AHWARN == false then AHWstr = "--ENAGE ALTITUDE HOLD--" else AHWstr = "" end if ALTWARN == false and XWARN == false and YWARN == false and APWARN == true and AHWARN == true and AUTOTWARN == false then AUTOTWARNstr = "--SELECT AUTO THROTTLE--" else AUTOTWARNstr = "" end if FLASH == true then FLASHstr = 255 else FLASHstr = 1 end
--On Screen TEXT if LG == true then LGstr = "Nav Lght:On" else LGstr = "Nav Lght:Off" end
if LL == true then LLstr = "Lnd Lght:On" else LLstr = "Lnd Lght:Off" end if AP == true then APstr = "AP:On" else APstr = "AP:Off" end if ALTH == true then ALTHstr = "Alt Hold:On" else ALTHstr = "Alt Hold:Off" end
--setting text color screen.setColor(tx.r,tx.g,tx.b,tx.t) --text speed screen.drawText(7,h-10,"Knots:") screen.drawText(40,h-10,SPD) --text Alt Hold screen.drawText(95,13,ALTHstr) --text Autopilot screen.drawText(7,13,APstr) --text braring screen.drawText(7,h-18,"Bearing:") screen.drawText(50,h-18,BEA) --text altitude screen.drawText(w-28-(string.len(ALT)*5),h-10,"Alt:") screen.drawText(w-5-(string.len(ALT)*5),h-10,ALT) --text Nav Lights screen.drawText(7,5,LGstr) --text landing Lights screen.drawText(95,5,LLstr) --System start text screen.setColor(253,179,0,FLASHstr) screen.drawText(w/2-65,h/2,ALTWARNstr) screen.drawText(w/2-74,h/2,XYWARNstr) screen.drawText(w/2-55,h/2,APWstr) screen.drawText(w/2-55,h/2,AHWstr) screen.drawText(w/2-60,h/2,AUTOTWARNstr) screen.setColor(0,0,0,FLASHSPDstr) screen.drawRectF(w/2-30, h/2-11, 63, 7) screen.setColor(0,0,0,FLASHBATTstr) screen.drawRectF(w/2-30, h/2-11, 65, 7) screen.setColor(255,0,0) screen.drawText(w/2-30,h/2-10,SPEEDWARNstr) screen.drawText(w/2-30,h/2-10,BATTWARNstr)
end
